          "media_kind": "epub",
          "section_id": null,
          "start_offset": 183,
          "text_quote_selector": {
            "exact": "\u201cTheorie und Praxis,\u201d Zeitsch. des Oesterreichischen Ingenieur u. Architecten-Vereines, 1905, Nr. 4 u. 6. I find a still more radical pragmatism than Ostwald\u2019s in an address by Professor W. S. Franklin: \u201cI think that the sickliest notion of physics, even if a student gets it, is that it is \u2018the science of masses, molecules and the ether.\u2019 And I think that the healthiest notion, even if a student does not wholly get it, is that physics is the science of the ways of taking hold of bodies and pushing them!\u201d (Science, January 2, 1903.) \u21a9\ufe0e"
          },
          "type": "epub_fragment_offsets"
